#Text=Pärnu
#Text=Pärnu is a resort seaside city ( and Estonia 's summer capital ) with a small harbour in south-western Estonia .
#Text=Understand
#Text=The city is known for its spas , shallow white sandy beach and beautiful parks .
#Text=It is also a popular place for conferences , theatre performances and concerts .
#Text=In 1838 the first spa was opened and nowadays
#Text=Pärnu is a health resort of international stature .
#Text=During the Great Northern War , the University of Tartu was relocated to Pärnu from 1699-1710 .
#Text=Tartu University still has a branch campus there today .
#Text=Since 1996
#Text=Pärnu has been known as Estonia 's Summer Capital .
#Text=Beach life , dozens of festivals , night clubs , big party crowds , concerts and funfairs - Pärnu has it all .
#Text=Pärnu is an ancient Hanseatic town where a medieval festival and an arts and crafts fair are held every summer .
#Text=Tourist Information Centre , Uus 4 , ☏ +3724473000 , ✉ parnu@visitestonia.com .
#Text=Get in
#Text=See Estonia#Get around for bus and train schedules .
#Text=By bus
#Text=Buses arrive at the small bus station ( bussijaam ) on the border of the old town .
#Text=This bus station feels like a big bus stop because the terminal building is somewhat hidden on the opposite side of the street .
#Text=Note a fast-food kiosk nearby .
#Text=It opens early in the morning and caters to morning travellers while the whole city is still sleeping .
#Text=Buses from Tallinn depart every hour and reach Pärnu in about two hours .
#Text=You can also travel from Viljandi ( 1 h ) and Tartu ( 2.5-3 h ) , Kuressaare ( 3 h ) , and Valga ( 2.5 h ) .
#Text=There is one daily bus from Saint Petersburg in Russia with a stop in Narva ( 5 h ) .
#Text=Check the schedules at here .
#Text=Pärnu is a major stop in the middle of the Tallinn – Riga route .
#Text=Buses run every 1-2 hours and connect you to the Latvian capital in 2.5 h. Pärnu can be an excellent stopover on your away between the Baltic capitals .
#Text=By train
#Text=Pärnu has a train connection to Tallinn .
#Text=Trains depart from Tallinn and from Pärnu twice a day .
#Text=The journey takes about 3 hours , check the Edelaraudtee website for the current schedule .
#Text=The station building has been razed down recently , so the train drops you at some strange place 3 km south of the city center ( reachable by city bus , though ) .
#Text=In contrast to Tartu , train connections to Pärnu are underdeveloped and remain inferior to the abundant bus options .
#Text=By car
#Text=Pärnu has road connections to Tallinn ( 128 km ) , Haapsalu ( 108 km ) , Tartu ( 174 km ) , as well as to Riga in Latvia ( 184 km ) .
#Text=The major artery of the Baltic states , Via Baltica , passes near Pärnu .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Pärnu airport ( EPU ) ( is 4 km north-west of the city ) .
#Text=It has some regular flights , but you are more likely to use this airport for continuing your journey from Pärnu rather than for traveling to the city .
#Text=Luftverkehr Friesland-Harle operates flights to the islands of Ruhnu ( regular ) and Kihnu ( on request only ) .
#Text=The Ruhnu flight continues to Kuressaare and costs about € 25 for each flight segment .
#Text=By boat
#Text=Pärnu has a large port , which is mostly used for cargo traffic .
#Text=Ferries to the island of Kihnu depart from the Munalaid dock located 35 km west of Pärnu .
#Text=However , a small passenger harbor exists at Kalda 2 ( right at the city center ) and may serve occasional weekend ferries to Kihnu and Ruhnu .
#Text=If you are arriving by sail boat ( keelyacht ) , you can dock at the Pärnu Yacht Club .
#Text=To stay with motorboat you can use Talvesadam on Pärnu moat ( Pärnu vallikraav ) .
#Text=Pärnu moat on Google map .
#Text=By bus
#Text=The bus network covers the whole city , including the suburbs .
#Text=There are 26 routes and their schedules can be found at Pärnu ATP-s website .
#Text=By foot
#Text=Pärnu 's old town is pretty small and navigable by foot and it 's full of small boutiques .
#Text=Lots of them are on Rüütli street .
#Text=See
#Text=The old town with buildings even from Medieval times .
#Text=Beautiful wooden villas .
#Text=The beach park and promenade .
#Text=Art galleries .
#Text=Lydia Koidula and Modern Art Museum and City gallery
#Text=Pärnu Town Hall , Nikolai tn 3 .
#Text=The Town Hall is located in a house built in 1797 by the merchant P.R. Harder .
#Text=In 1804 , the Russian czar Alexander I stayed in this house during his visit to Pärnu .
#Text=A new art nouveau building with neo-baroque details was completed in 1911 to the north side of the town hall .
#Text=Church of Jekaterina , Vee tn 8 .
#Text=Completed in 1768 , the Church of Jekaterina is the most style pure and ample baroque church in Estonia .
#Text=The church has influenced the development of orthodox church architecture in whole Balticum .
#Text=To this day Pärnu Russian congregation operates in the church .
#Text=Seegi Maja ( the Almshouse ) , Hospidali tn 1 .
#Text=Seegi Maja ( the Almshouse ) is known to be the oldest building in Pärnu .
#Text=It was built in 1658 on the remains of the old almshouse of the Holy Spirit 's Church as a shelter to the sick and the cripples .
#Text=Based on research on the wooden raft under the basement of the building , the old almshouse dates back to 1250-1350 .
#Text=The building was restored to look the way it did in the 17th century .
#Text=It houses the St. Peterburg Hotel and the restaurant Seegi Maja .
#Text=Statue of Raimond Valgre , Mere puiestee 22 .
#Text=The musician Raimond Valgre who played in Pärnu in 1930s and brought the town a lot of fame , can today be found sitting in the park near Kuursaal , as a bronze statue .
#Text=You too can sit down next to the beloved Estonian composer and enjoy his beautiful compositions .
#Text=Eliisabet 's Church , Nikolai tn 22 .
#Text=Eliisabet 's Church , inaugurated in 1750 , is the most outstanding sacral building of the Baroque period in Estonia .
#Text=One of the best organs in Estonia is in Eliisabet 's Church and the place is popular as a concert hall among music lovers .
#Text=Do
#Text=The Pärnu Jetty , Seedri tn 6 , Pärnu .
#Text=The jetty has gained a romantic aura as a place for lovers to take walks on ; however , before taking a walk there , be sure to check the water level !
#Text=The length of both jetties is a bit over two kilometres .
